The Shieldhaven Academy

Adventurer's Guild

Influence: Realm wide

Purpose: To guide, care for and protect the innocents of the land
Beliefs: No matter how you start in life, there is always room for greater potential
Leader: Headmaster Elias Ironmantle (Wise Elder) Symbol: A Silver Shield
Headquarters: The Shieldhaven Academy in Sentinel's Rest
Current Goal: Gather Knowledge & Protect a Secret Allies: The Silver Hand
Enemies:

Traits: Controls the ebb and flow of adventurers throughout the realm

Tasks:

  • Train Members

Relationships to other Factions:

  • Does business with The Illuminated
  • Is strongly allied with The Silver Hand

The Shieldhaven Academy is a place where orphans are sent when they have no where else to go. The children are taught to be adventurers and they provide everything they need until they can pass their exit adventure. Many children try to take it early but do not ever return -- either running away or dying in the process.

Locations

The Scholar's Hall: The location where book learning takes place consisting of a vast library of knowledge and a number of lecture halls.

The Dormitory: The location where all of the orphaned children sleep and where any studying adventurers can stay.

The Lodge: The location where visiting adventurers can pay to stay while they are using The Shieldhaven Academy facilities.

The Armory: The location where all training and supplied weapons and gear are stored.

Training Grounds: The location where physical and magical combat is taught and practiced consisting of a several small arenas, one large tournament arena, a shooting range and the stables.

The Tower: The location where all magic is practiced from alchemy to writing new spells and calling upon the favor of a god or patron.

Headmaster Elias Ironmantle

Elias Ironmantle was once a Gladiator. He is a human in his late 50s. He has silver-gray hair that he keeps short and neat. He sports a well-groomed beard. He has piercing blue eyes. He wears a dark blue military style coat with silver accents. He often carries a steel-tipped cane -- mostly for show.

Elias Ironmatle is stern but fair. He believes in discipline and the value of hard work. He has a soft spot for the orphans under his care, seeing their potential to rise above their circumstances, just as he did. Though he rarely shows his care and concern to the individuals.

Elias Ironmantle is dedicated to molding the next generation of adventures into honorable and capable individuals. He instills in his students a sense of duty and loyalty.

Elias Ironmantle often quotes old military sayings and expects punctuality in all things. Secretly he enjoys quite moments in the academy's garden, tending to a small collection of exotic plants.
